      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 27
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six. This high-revving power plant utilizes individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a sharp, linear throttle response all the way to its 8,000 RPM redline. The 6-speed Getrag manual transmission pairs with a factory-calibrated limited-slip differential for optimal power delivery. Significant mechanical updates include a reinforced rear subframe and a comprehensive VANOS overhaul to ensure long-term reliability. The chassis has been further refined with a Bilstein coilover setup and polyurethane bushings, enhancing turn-in precision and damping control. While the exterior shows an honest patina consistent with a well-maintained driver, the powertrain and suspension geometry remain dialed for peak performance.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 27
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Reliable daily driver. Clean title. Minor cosmetic wear. Engine runs strong. Well-maintained interior.",
      "price": 31500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 27
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "This vehicle has been meticulously maintained and remains in impressive condition, perfect for someone seeking reliability without the new-car price tag. The exterior finish retains a high-gloss luster, though a close inspection reveals a few minor stone chips on the hood and a small scuff on the rear passenger-side wheel arch. All glass is clear and free of cracks. Inside, the cabin is clean and smoke-free; the premium upholstery is in excellent shape, showing only slight softening on the driver\u2019s seat bolster. All electronic components, including the infotainment system, backup camera, and heated seats, are fully operational. Mechanically, the car is sound; the engine idles quietly, and the transmission shifts smoothly through all gears. It has been serviced regularly at 5,000-mile intervals, and I have the records to prove it. The tires are matching sets with plenty of tread depth left for several seasons of driving. This is a well-cared-for example that is ready for its next owner.",
      "price": 32500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 27
    },
    {
